value.value: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an ornamental border consisting of short straight or twisted threads or strips hanging from cut or raveled edges or from a separate band.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of a bowl.
Mobility relative to a second entity.

definition.value: For example, distinct anteroposterior mobility of palatine relative to mesethmoid.

value.value: Immobility relative to a second entity.

definition.value: For example: distinct anteroposterior immobility of palatine relative to mesethmoid.

value.value: A shape that is in the form of a plug, being tube-like and expanded on one end.
An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsomedially.
A shape that is in the form of a narrow strip encircling an object.
A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape resembling that of a trough, being narrow, long, and boxlike in shape.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having five angles and five sides.
A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms is abnormal.
Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

definition.value: Female quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the ovaries and/or uterus from surgical removal.

value.value: The bearer of this quality has_part n=1 of the indicated entity type, where n is bilaterally paired for a comparable organism..

definition.value: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being expanded laterally and or opened outward in shape.

value.value: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed distomedially, ie, pertaining to an inside aspect, but also farther away from the center of the body.
The bearer of this quality has_part n=2 of the indicated entity type, where n is unpaired for a comparable organism.
A structural quality which is held by a bearer where a localized pathological or traumatic structural change, damage, deformity, or discontinuity of tissue, organ, or body part is present.

definition.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by interruptions or gaps.
This term is intended for use for terms such as MP:0010461 discontinuous pulmonary artery and MP:0004157 interrupted aortic arch.

value.value: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's haploid cells undergo chromosome doubling.
An organismal quality of having successfully reproduced.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer being shielded from visible light.

definition.value: Shaded does not refer to radiation more generally, as this would be more shielded than shaded.
A width and length quality which is relatively small, where both width and length are decreased.
A width and length quality that is relatively large, where both width and length are increased.

value.value: A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively high.
A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively low.
A broken quality where an entity is cracked or broken, usually a bone.
A fractured quality where the fracture traverses the bone perpendicular to the axis of the bone.
A fractured quality in which one of the fragments is driven into another fragment.
A fractured quality where the fracture runs parallel to the long axis of a bone.
A fractured quality where the fracture occurs at a plane oblique to the long axis of the bone.
A fractured quality that occurs when torque (a rotating force) is applied along the axis of a bone.
A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.
A fractured quality in which the fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.
A decreased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decreased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: decreased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: An increased quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's increased magnitude in proportion to the magnitude of another entity.

definition.value: Example: increased proportion of CD4 T cells relative to total T cells.

value.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's components being torn, typically used for soft tissues or membranes.
The rate or speed of the change in in number of a population.
The rate or speed of the change in size of an individual entity.
Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

definition.value: Moved to a child of wholeness because broken implies a trauma and fragmented could be caused by a developmental process. See HP:0100168 Fragmented epiphyses as an example.

value.value: Red due to increase blood circulation in a defined area.

definition.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise male of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.
The term intersex is popular in use, but may be considered offensive when applied to humans. DSD can be expanded multiple ways to 'disorders/differences of sexual development/differentiation'.

value.value: A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have two stamens.
A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have only one stamen.
A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to male at a later life stage.
A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to female at a later life stage.
A protogynous quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.
A protandrous quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

definition.value: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise female of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.
The term intersex is popular in use, but may be considered offensive when applied to humans. DSD can be expanded multiple ways to 'disorders/differences of sexual development/differentiation'.

value.value: A quality inhering in a process by virtue of that process having a population or part of a population, where population is defined as a collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class distinguished by one or more characteristics, as participants.
A quality denoting the lack of a physical entity or object, such as a chemical.
